&lt;p&gt;IFS is seeking a Canvasser who can perform door-to-door canvassing operations nationwide. The Canvasser will walk door to door, utilizing a walk application on their smartphone. He/she must be willing and able to work long hours. The ideal candidate will be familiar with grassroots advocacy. Canvassers will be paid weekly. Excellent for anyone seeking part-time or temporary work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Major Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Walks door to door asking questions to potential voters&lt;br&gt;Gathers data via a walk application&lt;br&gt;Works closely with team leaders to ensure accountability and quality control&lt;br&gt;Disclaimer: These job duties are not all-inclusive. The employee may perform other job-related tasks and responsibilities as requested.&lt;br&gt;Basic Qualifications&lt;br&gt;Speak, read, and write in English&lt;br&gt;Maintain a clean and professional appearance&lt;br&gt;Have a basic understanding of grassroots campaigning&lt;br&gt;Have the ability to work long days, walking outside sometimes under harsh conditions&lt;br&gt;The ability to work successfully in a team&lt;br&gt;Strong interpersonal skills&lt;br&gt;High ethical standards&lt;br&gt;Must possess an iOS or Android cell phone&lt;br&gt;High School diploma/GED&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Previous canvassing experience&lt;br&gt;Multi-lingual&lt;br&gt;Associates degree/professional certificates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Must be a U.S. citizen or legal permanent resident&lt;br&gt;Must be willing to undergo an initial background investigation&lt;br&gt;Must be willing to sign a non-disclosure agreement&lt;br&gt;Must possess a valid driver’s license&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Types:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time, Part-time, Temporary&lt;/p&gt;

